-- Grupo Simec Cut to `Equal-Weight' at Morgan Stanley on Market Share Losses
-- Eric Martin
-- 2010-07-12T12:10:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/grupo-simec-cut-to-equal-weight-at-morgan-stanley-on-market-share-losses.html

          
          
             Grupo Simec SAB, the unit of
Industrias CH SAB, Mexico’s largest steelmaker, was cut to
“equal-weight” from “overweight” at Morgan Stanley, which
said the company is losing market share.  
          
          


  


        